====Rhodophyce<U+00E6> <span style="font-weight: 400;">(red algae)</span>====

The [[rhodophyte]], or [[red algal]] chloroplast group is another large and diverse chloroplast lineage.<ref name=AJB-historyofplastids /> Rhodophyte chloroplasts are also called ''[[rhodoplasts]]'',<ref name="Wise<U+2014>Plastid diversity" /> literally "red chloroplasts".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefreedictionary.com/rhodo-|title=rhodo-|publisher=Farlex|work=The Free Dictionary|accessdate=2013-06-07}}</ref>

Rhodoplasts have a double membrane with an intermembrane space and [[phycobilin]] pigments organized into [[phycobilisomes]] on the thylakoid membranes, preventing their thylakoids from stacking.<ref name="Springer<U+2014>The Chloroplast<U+2014>Chloroplast shapes" /> Some contain [[pyrenoids]].<ref name="Wise<U+2014>Plastid diversity" /> Rhodoplasts have [[chlorophyll a|chlorophyll ''a'']] and [[phycobilins]]<ref name="RSTB<U+2014>Endosymbiosis of plastids" /> for photosynthetic pigments; the phycobilin [[phycoerytherin]] is responsible for giving many red algae their distinctive [[red]] color.<ref name="Biology<U+2014>Campbell & Reece 582<U+2013>592" /> However, since they also contain the blue-green [[chlorophyll a|chlorophyll ''a'']] and other pigments, many are reddish to purple from the combination.<ref name="Wise<U+2014>Plastid diversity" /> The red phycoerytherin pigment is an adaptation to help red algae catch more sunlight in deep water<ref name="Wise<U+2014>Plastid diversity" /><U+2014>as such, some red algae that live in shallow water have less phycoerytherin in their rhodoplasts, and can appear more greenish.<ref name="Biology<U+2014>Campbell & Reece 582<U+2013>592" /> Rhodoplasts synthesize a form of starch called [[floridean]],<ref name="Wise<U+2014>Plastid diversity" /> which collects into granules outside the rhodoplast, in the cytoplasm of the red alga.<ref name="Springer<U+2014>The Chloroplast<U+2014>Chloroplast shapes" />

====Chloroplastida <span style="font-weight: 400;">(green algae and plants)</span>====

{{plain image|File:Micrasterias .jpg|'''Diversity of green algae''' Clockwise from top left: ''[[Scenedesmus]]'', ''[[Micrasterias]]'', ''[[Hydrodictyon]]'', ''[[Stigeoclonium]]'', ''[[Volvox]]''. Green algal chloroplasts are characterized by their pigments [[chlorophyll a|chlorophyll ''a'']] and [[chlorophyll b|chlorophyll ''b'']] which give them their green color.|460px|right|top|triangle|#3cca48|image override=
